<html>
<title>Welcome to The Heritage Foundation's WWW Site</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg"><body background="paperh.jpg">
<center><img src="/heritage/thf_log2.gif" width=334 height=104 border=0 alt="Heritage Foundation logo graphic">

<h2><i><FONT SIZE="+2">W</FONT>elcome to the Heritage Foundation's World Wide Web Site</i></h2></center>

<img src="/heritage/bldg.gif" align=right width=285 height=418 hspace=10 alt="The Heritage Foundation building photo"> </a>
Richard Weaver's seminal book "Ideas Have Consequences" could be our theme today, despite the fact that it was published almost 50 years ago. The remarkable growth of the Internet proves again the power of ideas to reshape how Americans communicate with each other, and the world. <p>
The Heritage Foundation's World Wide Web site was created to spread the ideas of free enterprise, limited government, individual freedom, traditional American values, and a strong national defense, the same ideas which caused a political revolution in the 1994 elections. As Speaker of the House Newt Gingrich declared just after the election: "Heritage is, without question, the most far-reaching conservative
organization in the country in the war of ideas, and one which has had a tremendous impact not just in Washington, but literally across the planet." 
<p>
As a leader in both the political and communications revolutions taking place today, The Heritage Foundation will continue to demonstrate the power of our ideas well into the 21st century. 
<p>
<a href="/heritage/staff/feulner.html">Dr. Edwin J. Feulner, Jr.</a><br>
President
